Subtitle
14
15 TO PERMIT A RETIRING PROSECUTING
16 ATTORNEY TO BE AWARDED HIS OR HER
17 SERVICE FIREARM UPON RETIREMENT.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 16-21-147(b), concerning the powers of a
22 prosecuting attorney and a deputy prosecuting attorney, is amended to add an
23 additional subdivision to read as follows:
24 (5) When a prosecuting attorney or a deputy prosecuting attorney
25 whom a prosecuting attorney has authorized to carry a firearm retires from
26 service as a prosecuting attorney or deputy prosecuting attorney, in
27 recognition of and appreciation for his or her service to the state may be
28 awarded any firearm carried during his or her tenure as prosecuting attorney
29 or deputy prosecuting attorney.
